<HEADLINE>
FT  05 AUG 92 / Bovis wins Dollars 234m deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BOVIS, the construction arm of Peninsular &amp; Oriental Steam Navigation (P&amp;O)
of the UK, has won a contract to manage construction of a Dollars 234m
(Pounds 122.5m) commercial property development in Lincoln Square, New York,
Andrew Taylor writes. It continues the company's recent successes in winning
large international contracts, including one to manage the main building
works for the 1996 Olympic Games in Atlanta, Georgia.
The latest deal, awarded to Lehrer McGovern Bovis by New York developers
Millennium Partners, involves constructing a 47-storey building with 8,000
sq ft of residential and commercial space, cinemas and shops. Work should be
finished by December 1994.
</TEXT>
